Create a C++ class representing a thread-safe priority queue. Write a code snippet that demonstrates the enqueue and dequeue operations with proper locking mechanisms and comments explaining their purpose and working.

```cpp
#include <queue>
#include <mutex>
#include <condition_variable>

template <typename T>
class ThreadSafePriorityQueue {
private:
    std::queue<T> data_queue; // The underlying priority queue
    mutable std::mutex queue_mutex; // Mutex for locking access to the queue
    std::condition_variable data_available; // Condition variable for signaling data availability

public:
    // Enqueue an element with priority
    void enqueue(T const& item) {
        std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock(queue_mutex);
        data_queue.push(item);
        lock.unlock(); // Unlock before signaling to avoid deadlock
        data_available.notify_one(); // Notify a waiting thread
    }

    // Dequeue an element with the highest priority
    T dequeue() {
        std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock(queue_mutex);
        data_available.wait(lock, [this] { return !data_queue.empty(); }); // Wait until data is available

        T top_item = data_queue.front();
        data_queue.pop();
        return top_item;
    }

    // Check if the queue is empty
    bool empty() const {
        std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(queue_mutex);
        return data_queue.empty();
    }
};
```

**Explanation:**
This code defines a `ThreadSafePriorityQueue` template class in C++, which provides thread-safe enqueue and dequeue operations for a priority queue. The class uses a `std::queue` as the underlying data structure and employs a `std::mutex` (`queue_mutex`) to ensure mutual exclusion when accessing the queue. A `std::condition_variable` (`data_available`) is used to signal threads waiting for data to become available. The `enqueue` method locks the mutex, adds the item to the queue, unlocks the mutex, and then signals the condition variable. The `dequeue` method acquires the lock, waits on the condition variable until data is available, dequeues the top item, and then returns it. The `empty` method simply checks the queue's emptiness while holding the lock. This ensures that the priority queue can be safely used in a multi-threaded environment.

