This Java tool uses Spoon to parse the source code and identify clases and methods. It then applies custom checks to identify God Classes (classes with too many methods) and Spaghetti Code (methods with high complexity). For a more accurate detection, replace the simple complexity check with a proper Cyclomatic Complexity calculation.

Question 2: Develop a Python script that uses static analysis to detect "Feature Envy" and " Lazy Class" code smells in a Django project.

